<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>follow the plough • put one’s hand to the plough</xh5><p> <i>follow the plough—</i>be a ploughman or peasant: His boys <u>followed the plough</u>; and his girls went out to service.</p><p> <i>put one’s hand to the plough</i>—(also: turn one’s hand to the plough) begin a task (with the implication that one will persist at it): Ideala, having at last <u>put her hand to the plough</u>, worked with a will.</p> </entry>
